WEBVTT

00:02.628 --> 00:04.128
<i>Previously on</i> The Passage...

00:04.171 --> 00:06.130
- What now?
- We go back.

00:06.257 --> 00:08.340
Get Amy and get
you guys out of here.

00:08.426 --> 00:09.591
<i>Amy is my calling.</i>

00:09.677 --> 00:11.719
<i>My job is to protect that child</i>

00:11.804 --> 00:14.471
and all the promise
she holds out to the world.

00:14.598 --> 00:17.891
Martinez. Washington has
approved your security proposal.

00:17.977 --> 00:20.060
Cages now require two keys
used simultaneously

00:20.187 --> 00:22.062
on separate panels.

00:22.189 --> 00:24.398
Does Fanning ever talk to you
in his dreams?

00:24.483 --> 00:25.899
<i>The last thing he told me was.</i>

00:26.027 --> 00:27.484
<i>"We have work to do."</i>

00:27.570 --> 00:29.028
<i>Carter gave me the message.</i>

00:29.071 --> 00:30.863
Said we'd already changed
the world.

00:30.990 --> 00:33.365
<i>- What did you mean by that?
- You'll see.</i>

00:36.662 --> 00:39.163
- I don't want to die.
- So don't.

00:39.248 --> 00:41.206
<i>The next step
is right in front of you,</i>

00:41.250 --> 00:43.584
<i>-you just have to take it.</i>

00:43.669 --> 00:46.170
<i>What Fanning wants</i>

00:46.213 --> 00:47.899
is for you to believe
the worst about yourself.

00:47.923 --> 00:49.715
Don't buy it.

00:49.759 --> 00:51.091
<i>I don't want to be alone.</i>

00:51.218 --> 00:52.301
<i>You don't have to be.</i>

00:52.428 --> 00:53.886
<i>You can go anywhere you want.</i>

00:53.971 --> 00:57.097
Mama?

00:57.224 --> 00:59.141
Ain't nothing so bad
we can't fix it.

00:59.226 --> 01:00.768
What is this for?

01:00.895 --> 01:03.145
- Light your way.

01:05.232 --> 01:06.732
Hello, Amy.

01:11.864 --> 01:15.365
So, we're really gonna stick
with the silent treatment, huh?

01:16.494 --> 01:19.203
How'd you do all this, Amy?

01:19.330 --> 01:21.288
This is incredible detail.

01:21.373 --> 01:23.791
You got the homey feel,
you got this creak in the floor

01:23.918 --> 01:26.543
and the coup de grÃ¢ce
is that scent of bacon

01:26.587 --> 01:28.462
just wafting through the air.

01:28.547 --> 01:29.907
I've never seen
anything like that.

01:29.965 --> 01:31.965
What do you want?

01:32.093 --> 01:35.260
I want to know how a little kid
like you did all this.

01:35.387 --> 01:38.013
That's easy. I had help.

01:38.099 --> 01:40.224
Oh, from Carter. Right?

01:40.309 --> 01:43.018
Yeah, he's a good guy.

01:43.062 --> 01:45.312
He definitely has a soft spot
for you, doesn't he?

01:48.400 --> 01:50.234
Carter says I'm special.

01:52.321 --> 01:53.946
That I'm different.

01:55.074 --> 01:56.782
That's because you are.

01:58.452 --> 02:00.828
He also said
you would try to hurt me.

02:00.955 --> 02:02.830
That is not true.

02:04.500 --> 02:05.999
I'll tell you something
that is true.

02:06.127 --> 02:09.211
I wasn't nice to Carter
when he was turning.

02:09.295 --> 02:12.297
- Why?
- Because when you become

02:12.383 --> 02:15.425
what I am and Carter is,
it takes moxie,

02:15.511 --> 02:18.720
and I had to make sure that
he could tap into that power,

02:18.806 --> 02:19.930
that he was ready.

02:20.015 --> 02:22.182
Ready for what?

02:23.310 --> 02:25.686
For what's coming next.

02:25.771 --> 02:28.230
The end is near, my dear.

02:28.274 --> 02:31.358
I don't do riddles, dude.
Just say what you mean.

02:33.445 --> 02:36.196
All right, fair enough.

02:36.282 --> 02:38.031
Amy Bellafonte,

02:38.159 --> 02:42.327
I think that you are
truly amazing,

02:42.454 --> 02:44.830
and, if you'd let me,
I'd like to be your friend.

02:47.793 --> 02:49.585
Lungs are clear.

02:49.670 --> 02:51.920
Heart rate's slow and steady.

02:52.047 --> 02:53.922
What's happening?

02:54.008 --> 02:56.383
The girl is sick.

02:56.427 --> 02:59.052
Well, that's too bad.

03:01.000 --> 03:07.074
Advertise your product or brand here
